==English==

===Etymology===
From {{Gr.}} '''[[Μυκήναι]]''' (''Mykenae'') the name of the Ancient Greek city, from '''[[Μυκήνη]]''' (''Mykene''), in Greek mythology a [[Nymph]] who lived around '''Mycenae'''.

===Noun===
'''Mycenae'''
#An ancient Greek city in the NE [[Peloponnesus]] on the plain of [[Argos]], inhabited since about 4000 B.C.E

